How 'metadevices' could make electronics fasterHow 'metadevices' could make electronics faster Wed, 15 Feb 2023 16:15:15 GMT 30:02  63ed05130f09e70011a76194不https://shows.acast.com/nature/episodes/how-metadevices-could-make-electronics-faster 63ed05130f09e70011a76194元设备如何使电子产品更快让电子设备进入超快的太赫兹速度，以及认知变化如何改变社交媒体对年轻人的影响。满的<h2> 00:47 用于更快电子设备的元设备</h2><p>过去，提高电子设备的速度需要设计更小的元件，但电阻的增加阻碍了尺寸的进一步缩小。为了解决这个问题，研究人员展示了一种“元设备”，它通过将信号流集中到设备的特定区域来防止阻力增加。希望这种元方法将来可以用来制造更小的电子元件。</p><br><p><em>研究文章：</em> <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-022-05595-z" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Nikoo &amp; Matioli</em></a></p><p><br></p><h2> 06:27 研究要点</h2><p>美国低收入人群的服务等待时间如何更长，以及您的大脑如何在您睡着时听到警报。</p><br><p><em>研究亮点：</em> <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-023-00372-y" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>谁浪费更多时间等待？收入很重要</em></a></p><p><em>研究亮点：</em> <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-023-00354-0" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>由于专用脑回路，噪音会破坏深度睡眠</em></a></p><p><br></p><h2>08:52 社交媒体对青少年心理健康影响的研究空白</h2><p>在过去十年中，青少年社交媒体的使用水平和报告的心理健康问题水平都有所增加。人们非常担心这些趋势是相互关联的，但很难获得确凿的证据。 So how can scientists get a better understanding of what&#39;s going on? In a Comment article for <em>Nature</em> , researchers argue that, rather than lumping &#39;young people&#39; into one homogeneous group, future studies should consider where they are in terms of their development, as this could influence the potential impacts of social media use.</p><br><p> <em>Comment:</em> <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-023-00402-9" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>How social media affects teen mental health: a missing link</em></a></p><p><br></p><h2> 19:52 Briefing Chat</h2><p> We discuss some highlights from the <em>Nature Briefing</em> . This time, we discuss self-burying devices that can plant seeds in remote areas from the air, and scientists&#39; reactions to a talk by CRISPR-baby researcher He Jiankui.</p><br><p> <em>Nature Video:</